author: Inside Edition
description: A New York state middle schooler is accused of engaging in a sextortion campaign against his classmates since February.
title: Middle School Student Arrested For Sextortion #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Jimmy Kimmel will return to the air Tuesday night. The news comes after negotiations between the late night talk show host and Disney. "We made the decision to suspend production on the show to avoid further inflaming a tense situation at an emotional moment for our country," Disney said in a statement. But will the ABC affiliates, who have demanded that Kimmel apologize to Charlie Kirk's family, agree to broadcast the show? Kimmel's suspension sparked debate about free speech in our nation.
title: Jimmy Kimmel To Return To Air On Tuesday Night

author: Inside Edition
description: A high school football player tackled a much smaller player, and then belly flopped on top of him. 15-year-old Colton Mims suffered two broken vertebrae and had to be rushed to the hospital. Comments on social media called for the 15-year-old belly flopper to face serious consequences. The school in Kalamazoo, Michigan said the student athlete who flopped onto Mims made a "poor choice" and that "the behavior was addressed."
title: Belly Flop On High School Football Player Leaves Him Hospitalized

author: Inside Edition
description: Charlie Kirk's widow, Erika, forgave the man who murdered him. The 36-year-old former Miss Arizona was given a rapturous reception at the State Farm Arena in Glendale, Arizona. Also there was President Donald Trump and billionaire Elon Musk. The day began with a pipe band playing "Amazing Grace." There was Super Bowl-level security. People came from across the nation to attend the memorial service.
title: Many Gather To Honor Charlie Kirk At Memorial Service in Arizona

author: Inside Edition
description: In June 2024, Lulu Gribbin was attacked by a shark on Florida's Gulf Coast. She was rushed to the hospital with devastating injuries – she lost her left hand and right leg. When released from the hospital, she received a hero's welcome. Gribbin practiced walking with a prosthetic leg on a treadmill and had to relearn how to do tasks like putting on clothes and brushing her teeth. The teen launched the Lulu Foundation to support amputees, which can be found here: https://lulustrong.com/
title: Teen Relearns How To Do Daily Tasks After Devastating Shark Attack

author: Inside Edition
description: A fan in the audience suffered a massive heart attack during a comedian's performance. Worry etched comic Drew Lynch's face as people in the club raced to help. The heart attack victim is 83-year-old Richard Wende. Luckily, in the audience was a group of nurses who were enjoying a night out. EMS arrived as the nurses administered first aid. After lifesaving efforts continued, the elderly man woke up. Lynch and Wende spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Nurses In Audience Save Man Suffering Heart Attack During Comedy Show

author: Inside Edition
description: UCLA is conducting an experiment on the Santa Monica breakwater that was constructed back in 1934.
title: 'Barbie Beach' Experiment Turns Ocean Water Pink #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A 6-week-old calico kitten walked onto a New York City subway car. The stray delighted crowds as she pranced her way around the train car. When no one claimed the cat, kind-hearted Betsaida Mercado, who was headed to work, took matters into her own hands. Mercado took the cat to her home before quickly deciding to adopt her. After a trip to the vet, the kitten is now settled in and is named Emmie, a riff of MTA, as in Metropolitan Transportation Authority, which operates the NYC subway system.
title: Woman Adopts Adorable Kitten Found on New York City Subway

author: Inside Edition
description: The two travel vloggers who thought they were flying to Nice, in the south of France, but got on a plane to Tunis, Tunisia, are visiting Tunis on purpose this time.
title: Vloggers Accidentally Travel To Tunis Instead Of Nice #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It would have been hard for cops to lose this car during a pursuit in Southern California. The sparks flying from the back of the vehicle were so bright, they could easily be seen by news helicopters following the chase. KCBS reports the West Covina Police were hot on the trail of a narcotics suspect. The driver slowly fled police on the interstate, until he pulled over and made a run for it. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Minivan Bursts Into Flames After Suspect Flees On Foot During Police Chase

author: Inside Edition
description: In just a few seconds, a car and its driver made history. Aboard an Italian naval aircraft carrier, driver Fabio Barone used the runway as a speedway, attempting to set a new record for fastest car on a boat. His car of choice: a red and black Ferrari SF90. The challenge took place in the port of Chivitavecchia, outside Rome. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Ferrari Driver Sets Record for Fastest Car on a Boat in Italy

author: Inside Edition
description: Homeowner Adam Dziubinski and his family were eating dinner when the crash happened just feet away.
title: Suspected Drunk Driver Crashes Car Into Family's Home #shorts
